race.comment: ON THE PROWL (10) made good improvement at his second start beaten 1.8L at Geelong. He maps well today and will appreciate the longer sprint. John Allen goes on and this is a winnable assignment. The best of the competition all have to manage awkward barriers. ANGELOS (13) spikes his figures placing at Ballarat and it was a big effort after settling last from the wide gate. She peaks and should be belting home. TAAJWAR (12) debuts for a smart local stable and will be well prepared. Has the blinkers on and Currie rides. Keep safe. A couple of key scratchings means the race depth plummets after this trio. SAKER FALCON (16) next elect but prefer for a minor placing.
